legacy.full_text:
🚨🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿 BREAKING: Premier League charges Nottingham Forest and Everton with breaching financial rules.

Clubs facing points deductions charged by Premier League with breaching profit & sustainability rules.

Second charge this season for Everton, docked 10 points in November. https://t.co/7j1VVJtqsq

Nottingham Forest :  1 charge, PUNISHED 
Everton FC : 2 charges, PUNISHED 

Man City : 115 charges. No action. 

Corruption right in front of our eyes.

Whether @Everton deserve a points deduction or not is up for debate but I’ve never liked FFP. Surely there’s a better way of protecting the future of clubs? FFP protects the elite clubs and makes it near impossible for the chasing pack to compete.
